org.embulk.base.restclient.jackson

Class JacksonServiceValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.embulk.base.restclient.record.ServiceValue
      • org.embulk.base.restclient.jackson.JacksonServiceValue

  • public class JacksonServiceValue
extends ServiceValue
    JacksonServiceValue represents a value in a JSON response to be converted to an Embulk column value. JacksonServiceValue depends on Jackson JsonNode's as* methods if type conversion is needed. For example with Jackson 2.5.0, the JSON below is recognized as boolean true. 
    
 { "flag": "true" }
    The other JSON below however cannot be recognized as Embulk's boolean true because Jackson 2.5.0 recognizes only "true" and "false". 
    
 { "flag": "True" }
    See Also:
    TextNode#asBoolean Implement another set of {@code ServiceValue} and {@code ServiceRecord} if a different style of type conversion is required.
